section.section:
In determining the adequacy of any insolvency plan, the Commissioner may consider:
The existence of insurance to cover expenses incurred in continuing benefits after an insolvency;
Provisions in provider contracts obligating providers to continue to provide services to enrollees or subscribers:
Reserves;
Letters of credit;
Guarantees; or
Any other arrangement to assure that benefits are continued in accordance with the provisions of paragraph (1) of this subsection.
